## Description

You are given a positive integer n. You have to represent it as a sum of maximum number of parts (not necessarily distinct) such that each part is of the form 2^k−1 for some non-negative integer k.

Formally, if you write n as a sum of p parts, then the condition becomes:

There exist p non-negative integers k1,k2,…,kp such that n=2k1−1+2k2−1+…+2kp−1.

Among all representations of n as a sum of maximum number of parts, you have to find a representation where the maximum part is minimum.

### Input

The only line of input contains an integer n (1≤n≤1018).

### Output

In the first line, output an integer p — the maximum number of parts in which n can be represented.

In the second line, output p integers r1,r2,…,rp (1≤ri≤1018) — the parts in which n can be represented. If there are multiple solutions, print any.

### Example

#### Input

7

#### Output

3

1 2 4

#### Input

15

#### Output

5

1 1 2 4 7

#### Input

1

#### Output

1

1

#### Note

In the first example, 7 can be represented as 1+2+4. There is no way to represent 7 as a sum of more than 3 parts.

In the second example, 15 can be represented as 1+1+2+4+7. There is no way to represent 15 as a sum of more than 5 parts.

In the third example, 1 can be represented as 1. There is no way to represent 1 as a sum of more than 1 part.

